        	<div class="why-cho_inner">
        	<h2>Continuous Integration</h2>
             <div class="why-cho_inner_subtext"><img src="images/content-image.jpg" height=250 width=330>
Continuous Integration is the act of enabling developers to integrate their code with the work of others frequently, like many times a day. Upon integration, automated testing is initiated to verify the code to be integrated is error free. By integrating frequently, the software development process improves. Developers are able to get the latest code faster. Problems are detected and corrected quicker. 
<br><br>

    At WonderOps, we can help you set up your continuous integration platform using open source and/or free tools that are equally effective if not better than commercial offerings. The CI platform can be hosted in a public cloud environment keeping costs low. Where it makes sense, we can help clients embrace docker to improve speed and consistency in their CI processes. 
 
